ith the production; manager for additional resources to meet the targets with required quality control. Issued; the IPC, subcontractor monthly bills, variation, and evaluation statements; Studied the drawings and specifications to rectify the discrepancies. Prepared the scope; of work, request for proposals and terms & conditions for the sub-contractors.; Communicated problems at the site, updated design-related issues & informed the; targets to be achieved during the period by chairing daily meetings with the site engineer.; Drove productive work & reduced wastage by issuing the reconciliation statements.; Generated the evaluation statements for the proposals received and developed a proper; risk assessment analysis when reviewing proposals. Ensured contractor’s proposals were; as per local standards and specifications.; PRIOR WORK HISTORY; Isolux Corsan Ltd, India; Senior Field Engineer | Oct 2009 – Aug 2012; Carried out the casting of Precast Pretensioned girders and precast MSE wall barrier with; friction slab at the casting yard, one major bridge of span length 60m, 4 Vehicular; underpass and rigid pavement at the toll plaza.; Administered prestressed pre tensioned girders casting yard which is key for the project &; handed over around 600 girders as per schedule with zero girder failure. Handed over timely; with best planning & quality (Taken actions to minimize minor pinholes).; Performed initial and routine load test on piles by dynamic load, maintained load method; (reaction by both kentledge and anchor pile) as per IS 2911 part IV.; Rolled out the girders by taking proper safety measures.; Performed various type of foundations, such as pile and open foundations.; Issued the steel and concrete reconciliation statements at the end of every month.; Carried out the pre-constructional Activities, such as utility shifting (electrical & water; pipelines) & land acquisition.; Steered the construction of the temporary office buildings, foundations of the cement; plant & crusher & installation of the same.; GMR Highways, India; Senior Engineer (Structures) | Aug 2007 – Sep 2009; Started the major structures, such as major bridge, ROB containing pre-stressed girders,; post-tensioning systems and piling works.; Designed the working drawings with various dimensions & level details for structures.; Steered all the stressing activities viz., cable proofing, stressing, routing and preparation; of its relevant documents/calculations.; Looked after the fabrication of shutters for PSC girders.; Carried out the marking of girders, bearing pedestals & bearings as per site requirement.; NCC Ltd., India; Junior Engineer | Jun 2006 – Aug 2007; Led the construction of wells by well sinking method and Pile foundation.; Held responsible for managing the day-to-day supervision of site construction activities; for construction of well foundations connected with pump station.; LEADERSHIP BENCHMARKS"}]'::jsonb, 'F:\Resume All 1\Resume PDF\K. ANIL KUMAR.pdf', 'Name: K. Anil Kumar

